# world/cocoaui.list — the conditional Cocoa GUI world layer
# (docs/cocoa_gui_design.md §12.3, sprint_cocoa_gui.md CG1). Loaded ONLY by
# the UI worker via `frontend::world::load_list(vm, path)` AFTER the base
# world is up — never from world/world.list, so the CLI, the WKWebView GUI,
# and the base test suite carry none of it.
#
# Same format as world.list: one .mst path per line, relative to THIS file's
# directory; blank lines and #-comments skipped. Files reserved 63+ (01-62 are
# taken by the base world; verify with `ls world/`).
63_cocoaui_stub.mst
# MacvmDelegate (the C6 delegate/action-target registry) loads BEFORE CocoaUI:
# CG4's `CocoaUI startup` references `MacvmDelegate actionTargetOn:` for the
# Workspace ⌘P/⌘D target, so the class must be declared when 64 compiles. The
# list order — not the filename number — is what fixes the forward reference.
65_cocoadelegate.mst
64_cocoaui.mst
# CocoaBrowser (CG7) loads after CocoaUI: startup resolves it BY NAME and asks
# it to register its view, so the file is optional — remove the line and the
# shell simply has no Browser entry.
66_cocoabrowser.mst
67_cocoafind.mst
